{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RenderContext","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"WorkflowType","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":"> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"WorkflowType","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Workflow","preciseIdentifier":"s:8WorkflowAAP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/Workflow"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During a render pass, a workflow may want to defer to a child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"workflow to render some portion of its content. For example,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a workflow that renders to a split-screen view model might","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to child A for the left side, and child B for the right","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"side view models. Nesting allows for a fractal tree that is constructed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"out of many small parts.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If a parent wants to delegate to a child workflow, it must first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create an instance of that workflow. This can be thought of as the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model of the child workflow. It does not contain any active state,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply contains the data necessary to create or update a workflow","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"node.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The parent then calls ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"render(workflow:outputMap:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with two values:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The child workflow."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A closure that transforms the child’s output events into the parent’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Event"},{"text":" type so that the parent can respond to events generated by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the child.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the parent had previously rendered a child of the same type, the existing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child workflow node is updated."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the parent had not rendered a child of the same type in the previous","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"render pass, a new child workflow node is generated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The infrastructure then performs a render pass on the child to obtain its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Rendering"},{"text":" value, which is then returned to the caller.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow"]]},"abstract":[{"code":"RenderContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the composition point for the workflow tree.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext\/makeOutputSink()","doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext\/makeSink(of:)","doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext\/makeSink(of:onEvent:)","doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext\/makeSta